# Number of neurons in hidden layer
CL = 3
# Number of neurons in hidden layer
HL = 10
# Initialize weights
W2 = np.random.randn(HL,2)*0.01
W3 = np.random.randn(CL,HL)*0.01
b2 = np.zeros((HL,1))*0.01
b3 = np.zeros((CL,1))*0.01


print(X.shape)
print(W2.shape)
print(W3.shape)



# loop over epochs
n_epochs = 10000
lr = 0.003
for i in range(n_epochs):
    # Calculate scores and activations
    z2 = np.dot(W2,X) + b2
    a2 = np.maximum(0,z2)
    z3 = np.dot(W3,a2)+b3

    # Calculate Loss
    probs = np.exp(z3)/np.sum(np.exp(z3),axis=0,keepdims=True)
    loss = -sum(np.log(probs[y,range(4*N)]))
    #print(loss)
    
    # Calculate delta_L (here: delta_L = dJ) and chance in W3
    dJ = probs
    dJ[y,range(4*N)] = dJ[y,range(4*N)]-1
    dW3 = np.dot(dJ,a2.T)
    
    # Calculate delta_2 and chance in W2
    delta_2 = np.dot(W3.T,dJ)
    delta_2[z2<=0] = 0
    dW2=np.dot(delta_2,X.T)
    
    db3 = np.sum(dJ,axis=1,keepdims=True)
    db2 = np.sum(delta_2,axis=1,keepdims=True)
    
    W3 += -lr*dW3
    W2 += -lr*dW2
    b3 += -lr*db3
    b2 += -lr*db2
    
    
print(loss)
   
# evaluate training set accuracy
z2 = np.dot(W2,X) + b2
a2 = np.maximum(0,z2)
z3 = np.dot(W3,a2)+b3
predicted_class = np.argmax(z3, axis=0)
print('training accuracy: %.2f' % (np.mean(predicted_class == y)))
